               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>The Shared Services Alliance (SSA) is a collaboration of the nuclear decommissioning estate’s client organisations. The following participating entities (PE) are collaborating for this procurement:</P>
                  <P>The NDA Entities participating in this procurement are Sellafield, Magnox, Low-level Waste Repository, National Nuclear Laboratories and Direct Rail Services. Other NDA Entities might be included in the final ITT adding to an additional value of 5 %.</P>
                  <P>We collaborate in the procurement of shared goods and services from the supply chain. We also act as the hub to facilitate and integrate supply chain management, development and engagement activities across the nuclear decommissioning estate. We work together to deliver value, in the alliance members by identifying opportunities to collaborate on common supply requirements. We seek to continually improve how we work and how we interact with the supply chain to deliver a successful portfolio of shared services that help the nuclear decommissioning estate to achieve its objective to be the nuclear client of choice.</P>
                  <P>"The Shared Services Alliance are looking for a supplier to provide:</P>
                  <P>Supply of maintenance repair and operations (MRO) tools and consumables.</P>
                  <P>Engineering Tools and consumables and associated services - incorporating but not limited to:- Spanners, Screwdrivers, Socket Sets, Insulated Tools, Crimpers, Cutters, Bolts, Screws, Fasteners, Compression Fittings, Clips, Washers, Fuses, Drill Bits, Padlocks, Key Cutting, Paint, Oils, Lubricants, Hand Tools, Power Tools and Tool Storage, Cutting Tools, Abrasives, Welding Consumables, Hoses, Nozzles, Non-Nuclear Commodity Filters.".</P>
                  <P>Requirements are of a general commodity nature in general standard quality requirements in accordance with ISO 9001:2015. A small proportion of requirements (~10 %) would have an elevated quality requirement of Quality Grade 3 in line with Sellafield CQR SLM 4.06.02.</P>
                  <P>Our current preferred solution would be that suppliers will be able to:</P>
                  <P>— provide a web-based order solution with bespoke catalogue capability,</P>
                  <P>— provide an e-catalogue solution that is compatible with a punch out from SAP,</P>
                  <P>— provide a solution for same day delivery for urgent and emergent requirements,</P>
                  <P>— demonstrate robust systems to ensure that counterfeit, fraudulent or suspect goods do not enter the supply chain,</P>
                  <P>— provide support for specific requirements of a more technical nature,</P>
                  <P>— provide the capability to place orders via customer nominated supply routes,</P>
                  <P>— Provide management information and KPI reporting that ensure supply performance is maintained,</P>
                  <P>— Provide demand management,</P>
                  <P>— Provide product standardisation and cost reduction.</P>
                  <P>A supplier engagement day is scheduled for 21 February 2018 at Hinton House, Birchwood Park Ave, Birchwood, Warrington WA3 6GR. Prior registration is essential. The number of organisations invited may be limited.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <INFO_ADD>
                  <P>See additional information in early supplier engagement documentation and questionnaire.</P>
               </INFO_ADD>
